returns and they come from a single source cash flow we focus on companies that are growing free cash flow and allocating it intelligently reinvesting cash flows in internal projects or acquisitions is preferred when those actions will generate returns above the cost of capital otherwise we believe company managements should return excess cash to shareholders through dividends share buybacks or debt repayments  collectively known as shareholder yield learn more  in the news bill priest appears on bnn’s money talk ceo bill priest appeared on bnns money talk where he discussed how the end of qe technology becoming the markets driving macro factor manuafacturing and the threat of protectionism market impact of the end of qe and rising rates watch segment why tech is the new macro watch segment manufacturing and protectionism watch segment see more  bill priest appears on cnbc pro ceo bill priest appeared on cnbc pro where he discussed a wide range of topics including the influence of technology on employment margins and payout ratios technology is the new macro watch segment full length video on cnbc pro subscription required see more  subscribe to email alerts stay up to date on epochs insights white papers and news about us people quarterly newsletter form adv careers stewardship code uk epoch insights white papers insights webcasts  transcripts video  audio investment approach investment philosophy investment process strategies  results us value us all cap value us small cap value us smid cap value us choice us equity shareholder yield global equity shareholder yield global choice global absolute return nonus equity nonus equity shareholder yield international small cap global small cap in the news epoch in the news the information contained on this website is distributed for informational purposes only and should not be considered investment advice or a recommendation of any particular security strategy or investment product information contained herein has been ob